  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good companies to work for in the Bay Area?",
  "response": "The Bay Area is home to a diverse array of companies across various industries, including technology, finance, healthcare, and more. Here are some well-regarded companies to work for in the Bay Area, known for their positive work environments, competitive benefits, and career growth opportunities:\n\n### **Technology**\n1. **Google** (Mountain View/Alphabet)  \n   - Known for its innovative culture, excellent perks, and focus on employee well-being.  \n2. **Apple** (Cupertino)  \n   - Offers a dynamic work environment and opportunities to work on cutting-edge products.  \n3. **Meta (Facebook)** (Menlo Park)  \n   - Known for its fast-paced, impactful work and strong emphasis on company culture.  \n4. **Tesla** (Fremont/Palo Alto)  \n   - Ideal for those passionate about sustainability and electric vehicles.  \n5. **Salesforce** (San Francisco)  \n   - Renowned for its strong corporate values, community engagement, and employee-centric policies.  \n\n### **FinTech & Financial Services**\n6. **Square (Block)** (San Francisco)  \n   - Focuses on financial inclusion and innovative payment solutions.  \n7. **Intuit** (Mountain View)  \n   - Known for its supportive culture and focus on work-life balance.  \n8. **Robinhood** (Menlo Park)  \n   - A fintech disruptor offering a dynamic and fast-growing environment.  \n\n### **Biotech & Healthcare**\n9. **Genentech** (South San Francisco)  \n   - A leader in biotechnology with a strong focus on innovation and employee development.  \n10. **Gilead Sciences** (Foster City)  \n    - Known for its work in life-saving treatments and a collaborative work environment.  \n11. **Verily** (South San Francisco)  \n    - A Google sister company focused on life sciences and healthcare innovation.  \n\n### **E-commerce & Consumer Goods**\n12. **Amazon (Lab126)** (Sunnyvale)  \n    - Known for its work on hardware like Kindle and Alexa.  \n13. **Adobe** (San Jose)  \n    - Offers a creative and collaborative work environment with excellent benefits.  \n\n### **Startups & Unicorns**\n14. **Stripe** (San Francisco)  \n    - A leading fintech company with a focus on payments and developer tools.  \n15. **Databricks** (San Francisco)  \n    - A fast-growing data and AI company with a strong engineering culture.  \n16. **Asana** (San Francisco)  \n    - Known for its focus on productivity and employee happiness.  \n\n### **Consulting & Professional Services**\n17. **McKinsey & Company** (San Francisco)  \n    - A top-tier consulting firm with opportunities for high-impact work.  \n18. **Deloitte** (San Francisco)  \n    - Offers a range of services and strong career development programs.  \n\n### **Other Notable Companies**\n19. **Airbnb** (San Francisco)  \n    - Known for its unique culture and focus on travel and hospitality.  \n20. **Twitter** (San Francisco)  \n    - Offers opportunities in social media and tech innovation.  \n\n### **Key Considerations**\n- **Culture Fit:** Different companies have distinct cultures\u2014research what aligns with your values.  \n- **Compensation:** The Bay Area offers competitive salaries, but cost of living is high.  \n- **Growth Opportunities:** Look for companies that invest in employee development.  \n- **Mission and Impact:** Many Bay Area companies are mission-driven, especially in tech and biotech.  \n\nUltimately, the best company for you depends on your career goals, interests, and priorities. Networking and researching company reviews on platforms like Glassdoor, LinkedIn, and Blind can also provide valuable insights.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
